API Documentation
Authentication
bash
POST /api/auth/register
POST /api/auth/login
POST /api/auth/refresh-token
Device Control
bash
GET  /api/devices                 # List all devices
POST /api/devices                 # Create device
PUT  /api/devices/:id             # Update device
POST /api/devices/:id/control     # Control device (on/off, temperature, etc)
GET  /api/devices/:id/status      # Get device status
Orders
bash
GET  /api/orders                  # List orders
POST /api/orders                  # Create order
PUT  /api/orders/:id              # Update order status
GET  /api/orders/:id/tracking     # Track order
POST /api/orders/:id/complete     # Mark as complete
Inventory
bash
GET  /api/inventory               # List inventory
PUT  /api/inventory/:id           # Update stock
GET  /api/inventory/forecast      # Get AI forecast
POST /api/inventory/restock-alert # Trigger restock
Analytics
bash
GET  /api/analytics/dashboard     # Dashboard data
GET  /api/analytics/sales         # Sales analytics
GET  /api/analytics/efficiency    # Equipment efficiency
GET  /api/analytics/waste         # Waste prediction
Full API docs: API.md

🏛️ MQTT Topic Structure
Code
kitchen/{kitchen_id}/
├── device/{device_id}/
│   ├── status              # Device status (on/off, temperature, etc)
│   ├── control             # Commands to device
│   ├── telemetry           # Sensor data
│   └── error               # Error messages
├── order/
│   ├── new                 # New orders
│   ├── update              # Order status updates
│   └── complete            # Order completed
├── inventory/
│   ├── alert               # Low stock alerts
│   ├── forecast            # Forecast updates
│   └── expiry              # Expiry warnings
└── staff/
    ├── attendance          # Attendance data
    ├── tasks               # Task assignments
    └── schedule            # Shift schedule
See MQTT_TOPICS.md for complete reference.

